b'Our teams across six continents have come together to wish the UAE a happy 49th National Day. :United_Arab_Emirates::keycap_4::keycap_9:
 
With patriotic shades of red, green, white and black, the show of national pride by our employees is inspired by the achievements of the UAE, as well as its significant place on the world stage as a leading transport, tourism and trade hub.
 
Click on our Instagram Stories to see our heartfelt greetings from across Africa, Americas, Asia, Australia and Europe, joined by our home Dubai.
 
#UAENationalDay49 #UAENationalDay #UAE #FlyEmiratesFlyBetter #EmiratesAirline'

b'We are getting ready to celebrate UAE National Day by showcasing rich Emirati culture, music and flavours at 40,000 feet.

Year around, we offer 36 channels on ice featuring Emirati music, shows, podcasts and films promoting the UAE\xe2\x80\x99s rich culture and history to the world. We are currently screening "My Story", the TV series based on the book of the same name by @hhshkmohd, Vice President and Prime Minister of the UAE and Ruler of Dubai.

This year, we will be serving local delicacies proudly crafted in the UAE, making travel a little sweeter in the airport lounge and on board. 

Customers travelling in all classes from 2 December will be able to savour chocolates from Dubai\xe2\x80\x99s only bean-to-bar chocolate maker, Mirzam.

We are also proud to support UAE-based businesses and local products. Over 1,600 small businesses and suppliers help us deliciously serve up everything from dates, nuts, juices and everything in between for a consistent onboard experience.

#UAENationalDay49 #FlyEmiratesFlyBetter #EmiratesAirline'

b'Delivering on our customer promise, we have completed an intensive programme to clear our backlog of refund requests caused by pandemic-related travel disruption. 

Over the seven-month period starting April, we processed nearly 1.7 million refund requests and returned AED 6.3 billion to customers in refunds. 

We thank our partners for their support and cooperation, and our customers for their understanding and trust.

Emirates will continue to lead the way in providing customers with travel assurance and confidence.

Click on the link in our bio for more details.'

b'Enjoy a complimentary night\xe2\x80\x99s stay in Dubai for layovers over 10 hours.

Dubai Connect makes your journey even more convenient and lets you explore our bustling city on the way to your destination at no additional cost.

Spend your day at sun-soaked beaches, heritage attractions or leisure facilities, there\xe2\x80\x99s always something to see in Dubai.

#FlyEmiratesFlyBetter #EmiratesAirline @Visit.Dubai @DXB'

b'In a new industry-first initiative, we are now offering our customers expanded, multi-risk travel insurance coverage in addition to our current COVID-19 cover.

Provided by Emirates and AIG Travel at no additional cost to customers, this cover is the first of its kind in the airline and travel insurance industry. 

You can now plan your travel and fly with even greater assurance and peace of mind with this truly unique offering designed for stress-free and hassle-free travel. 

Click on the link in our bio for more information.'

b'On World Children\xe2\x80\x99s Day, we are putting the spotlight on the work done by the Emirates Airline Foundation and its NGO partners to improve the welfare of disadvantaged children around the world.
 
Children are our world\xe2\x80\x99s collective hope for the future, and they deserve every dignity and opportunity. The Foundation currently supports 19 projects in 12 countries around the world including:
 
:child: The Virlanie Foundation in the Philippines helps provide housing and protection for 42 marginalised children.
 
:child: The Little Prince Nursery and School in Kenya provides nursery and primary education for over 400 underprivileged children from the Kibera slums.
 
:child: In South Africa, Singakwenza works to build sustainable early childhood programmes in economically disadvantaged communities and has trained over 1,400 parents, caregivers and educators last year.
 
:child: The Italian NGO Emergenza Sorrisi sent medical volunteers to perform life changing plastic surgeries for over 100 children last year.
 
:child: In India, IMMPACT provides education through community-based learning centers to 3,000 girls each year who come from underprivileged families mostly in rural areas that have little or no access to schools.

#WorldChildrensDay'

b'We will be serving the UK with more flights following the establishment of a UK-UAE air corridor. We are also increasing our A380 services to the UK and Russia to meet customer demand.

We are expanding our presence in the UK with additional flights to Birmingham and Glasgow, together with more @Airbus A380 services to London and Manchester.

Our iconic A380 will serve London Heathrow 4 times daily, Manchester 6 times a week, and Moscow daily.

@DXB @BirminghamAirport @GLA_Airport @Heathrow_Airport @MANairportUK @DME.aero

b'We have been crowned Best Airline and Best Long-Haul Airline in the UK.
 
We were named the Best Airline for 2020 at The Sun Travel Awards, and the Best Long-Haul Airline at The Times and The Sunday Times Travel Awards.
 
These wins underscore our continued commitment to offer a superior and safer customer experience in the air and on the ground across every class of travel.
 
Emirates was recently rated the safest airline in the world in its response to the COVID-19 Pandemic according to the Safe Travel Barometer.

@thesun @thetimes'

b'We have been rated the world\xe2\x80\x99s safest airline in our response to the COVID-19 pandemic according to the Safe Travel Barometer.

Emirates has topped the industry with a \xe2\x80\x98Safe Travel Score\xe2\x80\x99 of 4.4 out of 5.0 among 230+ airlines evaluated worldwide, as per an independent audit. 

We will continue to spare no effort to prioritize the health, care and safety of our customers, employees and communities.

Fly better and safer with Emirates.'

b'Emirates SkyCargo is deploying the @Airbus A380 on select cargo charter operations to transport urgently required cargo such as medical supplies to combat COVID-19 in regions experiencing a second wave of the pandemic.

The first dedicated Emirates A380 \xe2\x80\x98mini-freighter\xe2\x80\x99 successfully transported medical supplies between Seoul and Amsterdam via @DXB.

While demonstrating agility and innovation in business response to the pandemic, Emirates SkyCargo is working on further optimising the capacity of A380s through measures such as seat loading of cargo and has planned more dedicated A380 cargo flights in November.'

b'As we mark 35 years of flying better, we look forward to welcoming you on new journeys.\n\n#35yearsofEmirates #FlyEmiratesFlyBetter'

b'Our iconic @Airbus A380 will resume serving travellers between Amman and Dubai with three weekly flights starting from 4 November. 

In addition to the Jordanian capital, the Emirates A380 is now flying to Cairo, Paris, London Heathrow, Guangzhou and Moscow.

The Emirates A380 experience is sought after amongst travellers for its spacious and comfortable cabins and we will continue to expand its deployment in line with the gradual return in demand and operational approvals.

@QAIAirport @DXB'

b'Our new integrated biometric path at @DXB gives you a completely contactless airport experience from check-in to boarding. 

The state-of-the-art, hygienic contactless biometric path will improve customer flow through the airport with less document checks and less queuing. 

This is the latest in a series of initiatives we have introduced to make sure that travelling on Emirates is a seamless journey and gives our customers added peace of mind.

Click on the link in our bio to learn more.'

b'Emirates SkyCargo to set up the world\xe2\x80\x99s first dedicated air cargo hub in Dubai for the global distribution of COVID-19 vaccine.

Our fleet of modern and efficient all wide-body aircraft and a cargo network that currently spans more than 130 destinations across six continents, combined with the strategic geographic location of our Dubai hub, will enable us to rapidly move vaccine shipments worldwide.

#EmiratesSkyCargo #COVID19'

b'Happy World Food Day! Emirates SkyCargo is maintaining vital supply chains for food and perishables across its global network of more than 130 destinations during the COVID-19 pandemic. 

As a socially responsible carrier, Emirates SkyCargo has ensured that adequate cargo capacity remains available on its wide-body aircraft for the transport of urgent medical supplies as well as food items. 

We are currently transporting 500 tonnes of food items every day in the cargo hold of our aircraft across the world. 

We are proud to do our part to help countries and supermarkets maintain their food supplies while supporting farming communities reliant on food exports to make their livelihoods, in these challenging times.

#WorldFoodDay #EmiratesSkyCargo

b'We are proud to continue our support for Lebanon\xe2\x80\x99s relief efforts by delivering more humanitarian cargo.

As a global airline, we are committed to supporting local communities and will continue to provide more vital airlift to Lebanon.'

Emirates is also enabling people around the world to donate cash or pledge their Skywards Miles through the Emirates Airline Foundation in exchange for cargo capacity to transport critical goods and supplies to help people on the ground through recognised NGOs.

b'We are celebrating World Nature Conservation Day today by marking 20 years of partnership with the Dubai Desert Conservation Reserve (DDCR) and the release of DDCR\xe2\x80\x99s first annual report.

The Reserve covers an area of 225 square kilometres and makes up 5% of the Emirate of Dubai. A small area of the Reserve is allotted to tourism activity under careful controls and monitoring, and in the past year, it has attracted over 238,000 visitors.

Under the supervision of professional guides, visitors from around the world come to experience spectacular dune drives, desert safaris and traditional Arabian experiences. The guides also help visitors to appreciate and learn more about the desert\xe2\x80\x99s natural habitat, heritage and wildlife, and the importance of conservation.

The Reserve also works closely with local and international experts to protect and reintroduce indigenous species to the UAE.'

b'Our aircraft cabins are among the cleanest in the skies. b'This is not a goodbye but a \xe2\x80\x98see you soon\xe2\x80\x99 from your Emirates family around the world.

With nations closing their borders and going on lockdown, we have had to take the painful yet pragmatic measure of temporarily suspending our flights.

Whilst we have done everything possible to maintain crucial air links and get people to their loved ones, there\xe2\x80\x99s nothing more important right now than the health and safety of communities worldwide. 
This is an unprecedented crisis, and our thoughts go out to everyone affected.

We sincerely apologize to all our customers with travel disruptions. We hope to welcome you on board, as soon as feasible.

Our customers, Emirates Skywards members, partners, industry peers, employees, well-wishers and the communities we serve are at the heart of everything we do. We thank you for your continued support.

We thank our employee teams as well as the UAE government and regulatory bodies who have risen to this challenge and delivered beyond their call of duty. We appreciate your service.

We would like to express our gratitude to healthcare professionals worldwide who are at the frontline. You will never be forgotten.

We are confident that we will come out of this stronger than ever before. We are in this together. Now is the time for all of us to stay home so that we can take to the skies soon.'

b'In line with UAE government guidelines and as directed by our Chairman @hhahmedbinsaeed, our employees are now working from their homes. Those in roles that require them to be physically at work, are being supported in observing safe practices such as social distancing and hand hygiene. The health and safety of our employees is always a top priority, and we\xe2\x80\x99re doing our part to help safeguard our community.\n\n#StayHome #StayHomeStaySafe :copyright: @carlodxb'

b'Updated at 20:00 DXB time: 
Having received requests from governments and customers to support the repatriation of travellers, Emirates will continue to operate passenger and cargo flights to the following countries and territories until further notice, as long as borders remain open, and there is demand: the UK, Switzerland, Hong Kong, Thailand, Malaysia, Philippines, Japan, Singapore, Australia, South Africa, South Korea, USA, and Canada. 
The situation remains dynamic, and travellers can check flight status on Emirates.com. 
Today we made the painful yet pragmatic business decision to temporarily suspend most of our passenger flights by Wednesday, 25 March 2020.

The ongoing COVID-19 pandemic has resulted in significantly reduced global travel demand, accelerated by border closures, travel bans and country lockdowns. 
We will continue Emirates SkyCargo operations to maintain vital international air cargo links for economies and communities.

We are committed to preserve and secure the jobs of all Emirates Group employees in this difficult time; we will avoid job cuts.

We deeply apologize to our customers for the travel disruptions and inconvenience caused. We are committed to minimize customer impact. Learn more by clicking the link in our bio. 
We will continue to watch the situation closely, and will reinstate our passenger services, as soon as conditions allow.

These are unprecedented times for the airline and travel industry, but we will get through it with your support. 
Click on the link in our bio for more details about our announcement.'
